	Limes is a collection of C++ libraries providing both low-level utilities and high-level abstractions that I have found useful to have in a centralized location.

	Limes also provides a few small command-line utilities built using these libraries, and some CMake scripts for integrating Limes features into your build.

	Limes consists of the following @ref limes "libraries":

	Name                                 | Description                 | Dependencies
	------------------------------------ | --------------------------- | --------------------------------------
	@ref lib_limes_audio "limes_audio"   | Realtime audio utilities    | @ref lib_limes_vecops "limes_vecops"
	@ref lib_limes_core "limes_core"     | Core utilities              | None
	@ref lib_limes_midi "limes_midi"     | MIDI utilities              | @ref lib_limes_core "limes_core"
	@ref lib_limes_music "limes_music"   | Music theory utilities      | @ref lib_limes_core "limes_core"
	@ref lib_limes_vecops "limes_vecops" | SIMD operations for vectors | @ref lib_limes_core "limes_core"

	And the following @ref limes_programs "command line utilities":

	Name                                | Description
	----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------
	@ref file_util "FileUtil"           | OS-agnostic interface for a wide variety of filesystem tasks
	@ref binary_builder "BinaryBuilder" | Generates C++ source files which embed binary data files

	The following reference manuals are available:
	- @ref limes_cmake "CMake reference"
	- @ref limes_programs "Utility programs"
	- @ref envvar "Environment variables"
	- @ref dependency "Dependencies"
	- @ref docs_build "Building this documentation"

